sec.p:
Predictions using the identified 5-year lag between hydrography and cod recruitment show some success in terms of correlations (
  r = 0.49; 
  Fig 3e), but are less successful in reproducing the interannual variance (as measured by the Brier score; 
  β = 0.27). The larger uncertainty in the predictions is also seen from the wider spread in the cross-validated regression coefficients (gray shading). Nevertheless, our predictions are more skilful than that of random chance and lagged persistence forecasts for any lead times (not shown).
